Package org.neo4j.io.fs

Interface ReadableChannel

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable, Closeable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ReadableChecksumChannel, ReadableClosablePositionAwareChecksumChannel, ReadableLogChannel
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ReadAheadChannel, ReadAheadLogChannel
    public interface ReadableChannel
extends Closeable
    Represents a channel from where primitive values can be read. Mirrors WritableChannel in data types that can be read.

      • get

        void get​(byte[] bytes,
         int length)
  throws IOException
        Reads the next length bytes from this channel and puts them into bytes. Will throw ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException if length exceeds the length of bytes.
        Parameters:
        bytes - byte[] to put read bytes into.
        length - number of bytes to read from the channel.
        Throws:
        IOException - I/O error from channel.
        ReadPastEndException - if not enough data was available.
